# AI Providers

The playground spawns external AI agents via CLI tools. The provider abstraction is in `src/app/playground/lib/providers/`.

## Provider Types

| ID | CLI | Description |
|----|-----|-------------|
| `cursor` | `cursor agent` | Default. Uses Cursor's built-in AI agent. |
| `claude-code` | `claude` | Anthropic's Claude Code CLI. Supports effort/budget/turns config. |

## Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `types.ts` | `ProviderId`, `ProviderConfig`, `AgentSpawnOptions` interfaces |
| `cursor.ts` | Cursor CLI provider — `buildAgentArgs()`, `buildModelListArgs()`, `parseModelOutput()` |
| `claude-code.ts` | Claude Code provider — same interface, plus `ClaudeCodeOptions` (effort, budget, turns) |
| `registry.ts` | `getProvider()`, `getAllProviders()`, default provider lookup |
| `spawn-agent.ts` | Process spawning — child process with stdin piping, SIGTERM cancellation |
| `index.ts` | Barrel exports |

## ProviderConfig Interface

```ts
interface ProviderConfig {
  id: ProviderId;
  buildAgentArgs(options: AgentSpawnOptions): string[];
  buildModelListArgs(): string[];
  parseModelOutput(stdout: string): ModelInfo[];
}
```

## AgentSpawnOptions

```ts
interface AgentSpawnOptions {
  model?: string;
  effort?: string;        // claude-code only
  maxBudgetUsd?: number;  // claude-code only
  maxTurns?: number;      // claude-code only
}
```

## How Generation Works

1. User clicks "Run with Cursor/Claude" in the Iterate dialog
2. `POST /playground/api/generate` is called with the prompt and provider config
3. `spawn-agent.ts` spawns the CLI process, pipes the prompt via stdin
4. HTTP request stays open until agent completes
5. Agent writes iteration files to disk
6. File watcher detects `tree.json` changes → SSE event → canvas updates

